# Dataset
n_samples = 50

# Training
training_output = []
training_input = []
for idx in range(n_samples):
    x = np.random.rand(1) + 0.5
    t = myfunc(x) #+ np.random.normal(scale=0.01)
    training_input.append(np.array(x))
    training_output.append(np.array([t]))

# Test
n_samples = 5
test_input = []
test_output = []
for idx in range(n_samples):
    x = np.random.rand(1) + 0.5
    t = myfunc(x) #+ np.random.normal(scale=0.01)
    test_input.append(np.array(x))
    test_output.append(np.array([t]))

train = [training_input, training_output]
test = [test_input, test_output]

Normal (without momentum)¶

In [21]:
net_normal = copy.deepcopy(net_orig)
net = net_normal
wh = []
W1 = copy.copy(net.W[1])
b1 = copy.copy(net.b[1])
b2 = copy.copy(net.b[2])
cost = []
for k in range(500):
    # Try momentum = 0.01
    blah = net.__SGDv__(train, epochs=1, lrate=1., batch_size=50, momentum=0.01, progress=False)
    net.W[1] = copy.copy(W1)
    net.b[1] = copy.copy(b1)
    #net.b[2] = copy.copy(b2)
    wh.append(copy.copy(net.W[0][:,0]))
    cost.append(net.Evaluate(train))
whv_normal = np.array(wh)
cost_normal = np.array(cost)

With momentum¶

In [22]:
net_momentum = copy.deepcopy(net_orig)
net = net_momentum
wh = []
W1 = copy.copy(net.W[1])
b1 = copy.copy(net.b[1])
b2 = copy.copy(net.b[2])
cost = []
for k in range(500):
    # Try momentum = 0.9
    blah = net.__SGDv__(train, epochs=1, lrate=1., batch_size=50, momentum=0.9, progress=False)
    net.W[1] = copy.copy(W1)
    net.b[1] = copy.copy(b1)
    #net.b[2] = copy.copy(b2)
    wh.append(copy.copy(net.W[0][:,0]))
    cost.append(net.Evaluate(train))
whv_momentum = np.array(wh)
cost_momentum = np.array(cost)
